PURPOSE:-
--------
To verify basic RREP Generation and forwarding.



SCENARIO:-
---------

--------- means a link.
----X---- means a broken link

1-----2-----3



Node 1 sends 1 packet to 3.  Node 1 sends 1 packet to 2.

Since the packet for node 3 goes via Node 2 (node 2 forwards RREP
of node 3), node 1 learns that node 2 is a neighbor. Node 1 sends the
packet to node 2 before expiring the entry for node 2 in the route
table of node 1. So no RREQ should be generated by node 1 for node 2.


RUN:-
----
Run '<QUALNET_HOME>/bin/qualnet default.config'.


DESCRIPTION OF THE FILES:-
-------------------------
1. default.app -  QualNet configuration file for application input.
2. default.config - QualNet configuration input file.
3. default.expected.stat - QualNet statistics collection.
4. default.nodes - QualNet node position file.
5. README - This file.
